---
import BaseLayout from "../components/layout/BaseLayout.astro";
import ServiceSchema from "../components/schema/ServiceSchema.astro";
import EstimateModal from "../components/ui/EstimateModal";
import { business } from "../data/business";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Tree Trimming & Pruning Denver CO | 24-Hour Emergency Service"
  description="Professional tree trimming & pruning in Denver, CO. ISA-certified arborists. Free estimates, no trip charge. Available 24/7. Call (303) 949-6818."
  canonical="/tree-trimming"
>
  <ServiceSchema
    slot="head"
    name="Tree Trimming & Pruning Denver CO"
    description="Professional tree trimming and pruning in Denver, Colorado. ISA-certified arborists. Crown reduction, deadwooding, and bush and shrub trimming."
    url="/tree-trimming"
  />

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="relative min-h-[500px] md:min-h-[60vh] flex items-center overflow-hidden">
    <img src="/assets/hero-tree-trimming.webp" alt="Professional tree trimming and pruning service in Denver Colorado" class="absolute inset-0 h-full w-full object-cover" loading="eager" width="1920" height="1080" />
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-black/60"></div>
    <div class="container relative z-10 py-20 pb-28 md:py-28 text-center">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl leading-tight">
          Tree Trimming &amp; Pruning in Denver, CO
          <span class="block text-accent mt-2">Safer Trees, Better Property</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="mx-auto mt-6 text-lg text-white/90 md:text-xl max-w-2xl">
          Overgrown branches over your roof, fence, or power lines aren't just an eyesore - they're a liability. Our ISA-certified arborists prune trees properly, protecting your property and keeping your trees healthy long-term. Available 24/7. Free estimates. Call{" "}
          <a href={business.phoneTel} class="underline font-semibold text-accent hover:text-accent/80">{business.phone}</a>.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-8 flex flex-col items-center gap-4 sm:flex-row sm:justify-center">
          <a href={business.phoneTel} class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 rounded-md bg-accent px-8 py-4 text-base font-bold text-accent-foreground shadow-lg hover:bg-accent/90 transition-colors">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M22 16.92v3a2 2 0 0 1-2.18 2 19.79 19.79 0 0 1-8.63-3.07 19.5 19.5 0 0 1-6-6 19.79 19.79 0 0 1-3.07-8.67A2 2 0 0 1 4.11 2h3a2 2 0 0 1 2 1.72 12.84 12.84 0 0 0 .7 2.81 2 2 0 0 1-.45 2.11L8.09 9.91a16 16 0 0 0 6 6l1.27-1.27a2 2 0 0 1 2.11-.45 12.84 12.84 0 0 0 2.81.7A2 2 0 0 1 22 16.92z"></path></svg>
            Call {business.phone}
          </a>
          <EstimateModal client:load className="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 rounded-md bg-white/15 backdrop-blur border border-white/30 px-8 py-4 text-base font-bold text-white hover:bg-white/25 transition-colors">
            Get Free Estimate
          </EstimateModal>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 right-0 bg-primary/95 backdrop-blur-sm">
      <div class="container flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-x-8 gap-y-2 py-3 text-sm text-primary-foreground">
        <span class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-4 w-4 text-accent" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polygon points="12 2 15.09 8.26 22 9.27 17 14.14 18.18 21.02 12 17.77 5.82 21.02 7 14.14 2 9.27 8.91 8.26 12 2"></polygon></svg>
          <span class="font-medium">100+ Five-Star Reviews</span>
        </span>
        <span class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-4 w-4 text-accent" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="8" r="6"></circle><path d="M15.477 12.89 17 22l-5-3-5 3 1.523-9.11"></path></svg>
          <span class="font-medium">ISA-Certified Arborists</span>
        </span>
        <span class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-4 w-4 text-accent" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M4 14a1 1 0 0 1-.78-1.63l9.9-10.2a.5.5 0 0 1 .86.46l-1.92 6.02A1 1 0 0 0 13 10h7a1 1 0 0 1 .78 1.63l-9.9 10.2a.5.5 0 0 1-.86-.46l1.92-6.02A1 1 0 0 0 11 14z"></path></svg>
          <span class="font-medium">No Trip Charge</span>
        </span>
        <span class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-4 w-4 text-accent" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M16 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H6a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"></path><circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"></circle><path d="M22 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-3-3.87"></path><path d="M16 3.13a4 4 0 0 1 0 7.75"></path></svg>
          <span class="font-medium">Family Owned</span>
        </span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- OPENING -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
          That branch hanging over your roof has been bothering you for a while. Maybe it scraped the shingles during the last wind storm, or you noticed a thick limb pushing against your gutters. These aren't problems that fix themselves - they get heavier, weaker, and closer to causing real damage every season you wait. One good Front Range storm is all it takes to turn a maintenance issue into an insurance claim.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-foreground font-medium">
          Arbor Care Tree Solutions handles tree trimming and pruning in Denver with ISA-certified arborists on every job. That means every cut is made with the tree's structure and health in mind - not just cutting back what looks long.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SIGNS YOU NEED -->
  <section class="bg-muted py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="text-center text-2xl font-bold md:text-4xl">Signs You Need Tree Trimming &amp; Pruning</h2>
      <p class="mx-auto mt-6 max-w-3xl text-center text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
        The most obvious sign is branches that are too close to your house, fence, power lines, or other structures. But there are others worth watching:
      </p>
      <div class="mt-12 grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4">
        <!-- Warning: Branches too close -->
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-border bg-background p-6 text-center">
          <div class="mx-auto mb-4 inline-flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-destructive/10">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-6 w-6 text-destructive" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="m21.73 18-8-14a2 2 0 0 0-3.48 0l-8 14A2 2 0 0 0 4 21h16a2 2 0 0 0 1.73-3"></path><path d="M12 9v4"></path><path d="M12 17h.01"></path></svg>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">Branches too close to your roof, fence, power lines, or other structures</p>
        </div>
        <!-- Warning: Dead or hanging limbs -->
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-border bg-background p-6 text-center">
          <div class="mx-auto mb-4 inline-flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-destructive/10">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-6 w-6 text-destructive" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M17.7 7.7a2.5 2.5 0 1 1 1.8 4.3H2"></path><path d="M9.6 4.6A2 2 0 1 1 11 8H2"></path><path d="M12.6 19.4A2 2 0 1 0 14 16H2"></path></svg>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">Dead or hanging limbs that move differently in wind from the rest of the tree</p>
        </div>
        <!-- Warning: Dense canopy -->
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-border bg-background p-6 text-center">
          <div class="mx-auto mb-4 inline-flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-destructive/10">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-6 w-6 text-destructive" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M2 12s3-7 10-7 10 7 10 7-3 7-10 7-10-7-10-7Z"></path><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="3"></circle></svg>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">Canopy so dense it's blocking light or inviting fungal disease</p>
        </div>
        <!-- Warning: Heavy snow -->
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-border bg-background p-6 text-center">
          <div class="mx-auto mb-4 inline-flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-destructive/10">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-6 w-6 text-destructive" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="2" x2="22" y1="12" y2="12"></line><line x1="12" x2="12" y1="2" y2="22"></line><path d="m20 16-4-4 4-4"></path><path d="m4 8 4 4-4 4"></path><path d="m16 4-4 4-4-4"></path><path d="m8 20 4-4 4 4"></path></svg>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">Heavy wet spring snow loading onto unpruned, structurally weak branches</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mx-auto mt-10 max-w-3xl space-y-4 text-center">
        <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
          In Denver specifically, the combination of heavy wet spring snow and high winds makes unpruned trees a real seasonal risk. A large branch that's structurally weak doesn't need much to fail. The time to deal with it is before a storm, not after. Waiting until a limb falls means paying for removal and whatever it landed on.
        </p>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
          Crown density also matters for tree health. A canopy that's too thick limits airflow and light, which invites fungal disease and stress - especially in Denver's dry summers. Proper pruning isn't just about appearance. It's about keeping the tree structurally sound for years to come.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- OUR OPTIONS -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="text-center text-2xl font-bold md:text-4xl">Our Tree Trimming &amp; Pruning Options</h2>
      <p class="mx-auto mt-4 max-w-2xl text-center text-muted-foreground">
        Our pruning work falls into a few categories depending on what your trees need.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-12 space-y-8">
        <!-- Crown Reduction -->
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-6 rounded-xl border border-border bg-card p-8 md:flex-row md:items-start">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0">
            <div class="inline-flex h-16 w-16 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-accent/15">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-8 w-8 text-accent" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="m17 14 3 3.3a1 1 0 0 1-.7 1.7H4.7a1 1 0 0 1-.7-1.7L7 14"></path><path d="m17 14V2H7v12"></path><rect x="2" y="18" width="20" height="4" rx="1"></rect></svg>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex-1">
            <a href="/crown-reduction-denver-co" class="text-xl font-bold text-primary hover:underline">Crown Reduction</a>
            <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">For trees that have grown too large or wide for their space, we perform crown reduction - selectively reducing the overall size of the canopy while maintaining the tree's natural shape and long-term health. This is the right approach when a tree is encroaching on a structure or has become too heavy at the top.</p>
            <a href="/crown-reduction-denver-co" class="mt-4 inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-sm font-semibold text-primary hover:underline">
              Learn more about Crown Reduction <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-4 w-4" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="m9 18 6-6-6-6"></path></svg>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <!-- Deadwooding -->
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-6 rounded-xl border border-border bg-card p-8 md:flex-row md:items-start md:flex-row-reverse">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0">
            <div class="inline-flex h-16 w-16 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-accent/15">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-8 w-8 text-accent" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="6" cy="6" r="3"></circle><path d="M8.12 8.12 12 12"></path><path d="M20 4 8.12 15.88"></path><circle cx="6" cy="18" r="3"></circle><path d="M14.8 14.8 20 20"></path></svg>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex-1">
            <a href="/deadwooding-denver-co" class="text-xl font-bold text-primary hover:underline">Deadwooding</a>
            <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">For trees carrying dead, dying, or diseased limbs, we offer deadwooding. Removing dead wood eliminates falling hazards and stops disease from spreading to healthy parts of the tree. It's one of the most impactful things you can do for a mature tree that otherwise looks fine.</p>
            <a href="/deadwooding-denver-co" class="mt-4 inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-sm font-semibold text-primary hover:underline">
              Learn more about Deadwooding <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-4 w-4" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="m9 18 6-6-6-6"></path></svg>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <!-- Bush & Shrub Trimming -->
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-6 rounded-xl border border-border bg-card p-8 md:flex-row md:items-start">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0">
            <div class="inline-flex h-16 w-16 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-accent/15">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-8 w-8 text-accent" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="6" cy="6" r="3"></circle><path d="M8.12 8.12 12 12"></path><path d="M20 4 8.12 15.88"></path><circle cx="6" cy="18" r="3"></circle><path d="M14.8 14.8 20 20"></path></svg>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex-1">
            <a href="/bush-shrub-trimming-denver-co" class="text-xl font-bold text-primary hover:underline">Bush &amp; Shrub Trimming</a>
            <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">We also handle bush &amp; shrub trimming for properties where overgrown shrubs are blocking windows, crowding walkways, or getting out of shape. The same attention to proper technique applies - we cut for plant health, not just appearance.</p>
            <a href="/bush-shrub-trimming-denver-co" class="mt-4 inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-sm font-semibold text-primary hover:underline">
              Learn more about Bush &amp; Shrub Trimming <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-4 w-4" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="m9 18 6-6-6-6"></path></svg>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FOR DENVER -->
  <section class="bg-muted py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
        <div class="grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-5">
          <div class="md:col-span-3">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold md:text-4xl">Tree Trimming &amp; Pruning for Denver Homes</h2>
            <p class="mt-6 leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
              Denver's Front Range climate creates specific challenges for tree maintenance. Late spring snowstorms regularly bring heavy, wet snow that loads onto canopies and snaps limbs - especially on trees that haven't been pruned to reduce weight and wind resistance. We see the aftermath every spring across Denver, Aurora, Lakewood, Englewood, and surrounding areas.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
              High winds off the mountains are a year-round factor. Trees with thick, unpruned canopies act like sails in strong gusts. Reducing crown density through proper pruning dramatically lowers the load on the trunk and root system during wind events.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
              Drought stress is also a factor in Denver. Trees that are already weakened by dry conditions are more likely to have structural failures. Regular pruning - removing dead wood and reducing crown weight - helps stressed trees manage the load they're carrying. Our arborists work throughout the Denver metro and understand what local trees face season by season.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="md:col-span-2 flex flex-col gap-6">
            <img
              src="/assets/hero-climber.webp"
              alt="Arbor Care arborist climbing and trimming a tree in Denver Colorado"
              class="w-full rounded-xl object-cover max-h-[400px]"
              loading="lazy"
              width="600"
              height="400"
            />
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-border bg-background p-6">
              <div class="mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 text-accent" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M20 10c0 6-8 12-8 12s-8-6-8-12a8 8 0 0 1 16 0Z"></path><circle cx="12" cy="10" r="3"></circle></svg>
                <h3 class="font-bold">Service Areas</h3>
              </div>
              <ul class="space-y-2">
                {business.serviceAreas.map((area) => (
                  <li class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
                    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-4 w-4 text-accent flex-shrink-0" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M22 11.08V12a10 10 0 1 1-5.93-9.14"></path><path d="m9 11 3 3L22 4"></path></svg>
                    {area}
                  </li>
                ))}
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT TO EXPECT -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="text-center text-2xl font-bold md:text-4xl">What to Expect</h2>
      <div class="mx-auto mt-12 max-w-3xl grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-6">
          <div class="mb-3 inline-flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-accent/15">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 text-accent" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="2" ry="2"></rect><path d="m9 12 2 2 4-4"></path></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-bold mb-2">Free On-Site Estimate</h3>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
            When you call, we'll schedule a free on-site estimate at your property. One of our ISA-certified arborists walks the job with you, looks at the trees in question, and tells you exactly what needs to be done and why. You get a firm price before any work starts - no surprises on the invoice.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-6">
          <div class="mb-3 inline-flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-accent/15">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 text-accent" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"></circle><polyline points="12 6 12 12 16 14"></polyline></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-bold mb-2">Day of Service</h3>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
            Our crew arrives with the right equipment for the job. We prune using proper technique, clean up all debris, and haul everything away before we leave. Most residential trimming jobs are completed in a single visit. If something comes up that changes the scope, we tell you before we proceed.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHY CHOOSE US -->
  <section class="bg-muted py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="text-center text-2xl font-bold md:text-4xl">Why Choose Us for Tree Trimming &amp; Pruning</h2>
      <p class="mx-auto mt-6 max-w-3xl text-center text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
        Arbor Care Tree Solutions is a family-owned company with ISA-certified arborists on staff - that credential matters because it means our pruning decisions are based on tree science, not guesswork. We've earned 100+ five-star Google reviews from Denver homeowners by showing up on time, doing the work right, and charging what we quoted.
      </p>
      <div class="mx-auto mt-10 grid max-w-3xl gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 rounded-lg border border-border bg-background p-4">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 text-accent flex-shrink-0" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="8" r="6"></circle><path d="M15.477 12.89 17 22l-5-3-5 3 1.523-9.11"></path></svg>
          <span class="text-sm font-medium">ISA-certified arborists on every job</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 rounded-lg border border-border bg-background p-4">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 text-accent flex-shrink-0" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M16 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H6a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"></path><circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"></circle><path d="M22 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-3-3.87"></path><path d="M16 3.13a4 4 0 0 1 0 7.75"></path></svg>
          <span class="text-sm font-medium">Family-owned company</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 rounded-lg border border-border bg-background p-4">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 text-accent flex-shrink-0" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polygon points="12 2 15.09 8.26 22 9.27 17 14.14 18.18 21.02 12 17.77 5.82 21.02 7 14.14 2 9.27 8.91 8.26 12 2"></polygon></svg>
          <span class="text-sm font-medium">100+ five-star Google reviews</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 rounded-lg border border-border bg-background p-4">
